<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1983] WebConsole HttpContext should flush response after setting response status</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1983</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Web Console uses its own HttpContext implementation to handle authentication. When authentication is missing, it sets (or currently sendError) the response status 401/UNAUTHENTICATED but does not flush the response.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Felix Http Base code overwrites this to 403/FORBIDDEN if the response is not committed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So to ensure, the correct status is really sent, the handleSecurity implementation must flush the response.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12445389">FELIX-1983</key>
            <summary>WebConsole HttpContext should flush response after setting response status</summary>
